    "created_at": "2015-03-11T16:59:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-03-11T17:00:40Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "hi. i’m a linux user and i expect every configuration (except for historical things like vim and bash) to be in `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME`, not polluting my `$HOME`.\n\njust like every windows user expects things to be in in `%APPDATA%` or `C:\\Users\\%USERNAME%\\AppData\\Local\\` and mac users in `~/Library/Application Support/`\n\nlook [here](http://www.chromium.org/user-experience/user-data-directory) for how you’re supposed to do things. (approximately: while `XDG_CONFIG_HOME=~/.config/` by default, _the user_ can configure it to point elsewhere. but those users of course know what they’re doing)\n"
  },
