    "updated_at": "2015-03-11T17:18:13Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We've been over this plenty of times. We feel it's more important to be consistent across platforms than to try to comply with XDG specs. It's not that we don't know about the specs or how to comply with them, it's that we've weighed up the options and decided to do it with `~/.ipython`.\n\nIf it helps, IPython is now some 14 years old, so you can consider it historical.\n"
